  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Native Seeds from Our Land: Recovering the Agricultural and Food Culture of Coastal Small Farmers</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project &#x201C;Native Seeds from Our Land&#x201D; will be implemented in the canton of Pedro Carbo on the coast of Ecuador by FOCCAHL, a local small-farmer organization. Since the area is facing serious problems from monocropping, dependence on agricultural inputs, drought and feeble organization, the aim is to complement and improve families&#x2019; diets by diversifying farm production. Support will also include conserving water from family and community sources during the dry season. A total of 240 families will participate&#x2014;120 with original resources&#x2014; receiving seeds, trees, materials for fencing and animal shelters, sheep, hogs, hens and chickens. Training will include experience exchanges, workshops and meetings.</narrative>
  </description>
